Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Budock Urban 
    and Budock Rural.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parish of Budock Rural. See also Table 
    2, note (d).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Budock. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Falmouth, Budock and Penryn.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Budock in Falmouth 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.10.1920 and added to the parish of Falmouth.
Also known as Falmouth Town. Abolished 1.10.1920 and added to the parish of Falmouth.
